      "side": 1,
      "message": "not related to this CL, but this smells. Why do we call this func if there is no access token (shouldn\u0027t we raise an error instead)? If the access token is available *yet\", then shouldn\u0027t this.accessToken be a promise?\n\nalso repetition. Maybe use a decorator?",
